Package: circhelp
Type: Package
Title: Circular Analyses Helper Functions
Version: 1.1
Authors@R: c(person("Andrey", "Chetverikov", email = "andrey.chetverikov@uib.no",
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2767-6310"), role = c("aut", "cre")),
  person("Eline", "Van Geert", email = "eline.vangeert@kuleuven.be",
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7848-5998"),
  role = c("ctb")))
Description: A small helper package for circular data analyses, specifically aimed for psychologists and neuroscientists dealing with circular data. Includes light-weight functions for computing descriptive statistics in different circular spaces (e.g., 2pi, 180, or 360 degrees), functions to handle angle-dependent biases, padding circular data, and more.
